app.comment:
A library for creating a grid of squares. There are three versions - one for a fixed-size grid containing variable-sized squares, and two that create a horizontally/vertically scrolling grid containing fixed-size squares.

The library contains three demo pages. Start them, then tap the screen to increase the number of squares.

xnjN80AEri1QX2cSkS68y4yO.text: Grid of squares: Specify how to draw each cell, the minimum number of cells, and the total size of the grid. The algorithm automatically computes how big to draw the cells in order to fit.

GtoPHKZtc4RJV24oY5TXvzhb.text: Horizontally scrolling squares: Specify how to draw each cell, the minimum number of cells, the size of each cell, the group width (the algorithm inserts some space between groups), and the total height.

dIkmeEx19KrSL0e8iRzd4Zez.text: Vertically scrolling squares: Specify how to draw each cell, the minimum number of cells, the size of each cell, the total width, and the group height (the algorithm inserts some space between groups).
